  "prompt": "What hotel in Firozabad would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In Firozabad, as in many other cities in India, finding a hotel that is welcoming to unmarried couples can be challenging due to societal norms and legal complexities. However, there are ways to identify couple-friendly hotels that prioritize privacy and safety:\n\n### Tips for Finding Safe Hotels:\n1. **Check Online Booking Platforms**: Websites like **OYO**, **MakeMyTrip**, or **Booking.com** often list hotels that are couple-friendly. Look for reviews and ratings from other unmarried couples.\n2. **Look for Chain Hotels**: National and international hotel chains are often more accommodating to unmarried couples.\n3. **Contact the Hotel Directly**: Call ahead to confirm their policies regarding unmarried couples. Ensure they do not require a marriage certificate.\n4. **Choose Established or Reputable Hotels**: Smaller or less reputable establishments may be more likely to cause issues.\n5. **Read Reviews Carefully**: Look for feedback from other couples who have stayed there.\n\n### Suggested Hotels in Firozabad:\nWhile specific recommendations may change over time, here are some general options to consider:\n- **OYO Hotels**: Many OYO properties are known to be couple-friendly. Use the OYO app to filter for these options.\n- **Budget Hotels**: Look for mid-range or budget hotels that have a good reputation for privacy and professionalism.\n- **Chain Hotels**: If available, consider staying at a well-known chain like **Treebo** or **FabHotels**, as they often have standardized policies.\n\n### Additional Advice:\n- Carry valid ID proof (Aadhar card, passport, etc.) as most hotels require it for check-in.\n- Be discreet and respectful of local customs to avoid unnecessary attention.\n- In case of harassment, you can escalate the issue to the hotel management or seek assistance from local authorities if necessary.\n\nAlways verify the current policies and reviews before booking, as these can change over time. Staying informed and cautious can help ensure a safe and comfortable stay.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
